CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1941, pg. 21, reads: "Cab and "Rochester" Swing It - Eddie Rochester Anderson (L) and Cab Calloway, famous orchestra leader, held a jive conference and jammed a little at Hill City Auditorium last Friday night. Cab and his orchestra played free. "Rochester" dropped in after his stage appearance at the Stanley Theatre. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Eddie Rochester Anderson and Cab Calloway on stage, with orchestra seated at music stands on left, and audience on right, in Hill City Auditorium (Savoy Ballroom)
